The article is a memorandum from the White House dated January 21, 2009, titled "Transparency and Open Government." It emphasizes the commitment of the Obama Administration to promote openness, transparency, and public participation in government. The memorandum states that transparency is essential for accountability and that information maintained by the government is a national asset. It calls for the use of new technologies to make information readily available to the public and encourages public feedback. The memorandum also highlights the importance of public engagement and collaboration in policymaking and decision-making processes. It directs the Chief Technology Officer to coordinate the development of an Open Government Directive, which will provide specific actions for executive departments and agencies to implement the principles outlined in the memorandum. It concludes by stating that the memorandum does not create any enforceable rights or benefits.